@yxieca @taoyl-ms It is not very clear to me the usage of this file: deployment_id_asn_map.yml.  My understanding is this is used to set the remote-as in bgp configuration. For any upgrade,  we should keep all the configurations, including bgp configurations, I don't see why we should change the map during the upgrade even if new images have the new map.

For new switches builds, we could use the new map from new images.  Also, this file should be changed for different environment, it only gives default mapping looks like.

Let's me know your opinion, it is easy to remove that file from copy list but would like understand the reason.
